  "summary": "Malicious code in poly-provider-api (npm)",
  "details": "Poly-provider-api@4.6.1 is a trojanized package that acts as a remote code execution dropper. When the package is imported (require'd), it fetches a payload from hxxps://31[.]97[.]137[.]157:45000/icons/108 and executes it via the Function constructor with full Node.js context (require, process, Buffer, setTimeout, etc.), giving the remote payload full access to the host system. The package has no repository and its README describes a non-existent API management library that does not match the actual code.",
